Include Discontinued








Hinge Type



X
Hinge Type
Ball Bearing hinges are the go-to hinge for most applications, they tend to out perform plain bearing hinges in that they require less maintenance and produce less wear and less noise.



Mortise Hinges are recessed into the door and the jamb which allows the door to close completely. Typically these hinges are also much more wear and weather resistant, as well as heavier duty than your standard ball bearing hinge.



Plain Bearing Hinges are most often the cheap alternative to Ball Bearing Hinges. These hinges produce the most wear on their internals and are often noise makers if not maintained well. They are a great alternative for upgrades on a tight budget.



Spring Hinges are great when used as screen door closers or cabinet door closers. These hinges are designed for light weight doors and ensure the door is kept closed automatically.



Strap Hinges are decorative and functional. These hinges are common on barn doors and can give you a rustic or traditional look if thats what you desire.








										Ball Bearing
										(6)





										Plain Bearing
										(17)









Hinge Size



X
Hinge Size
	Use this field to narrow your results by hinge size.






